properties.name: CALGARY
properties.popup:
University of Calgary

Serological Testing to Outline Protocols for COVID-19 in Inflammatory Bowel Disease (STOP COVID-19 in IBD) is a prospective, observational cohort study of adults with IBD who are followed for serological response to vaccination against SARS-CoV-2. The study examines serological response follwing the 1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th dose of SARS-CoV-2 vaccines in those with IBD, and measures the decay of antibodies over time and the factors, including medications, associated with antibody levels. See Quan 2021 and Quan 2022 for more information.

Click here to view the STOP COVID-19 in IBD ShinyApp with corresponding data and visualizations.
